Reasoning: The paper discusses attacks against cryptosystems, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The attacks are based on the decoding of sparse parity-check codes, which is related to information theory (cs.IT) and error-correcting codes (cs.CC). The paper also discusses side-channel information leakages, which is related to software engineering (cs.SE) and cryptography (cs.CY).
